They say change is the only constant, but in my life, sometimes it feels like change is the only thing. 

I’ve always been someone who gets bored easily constantly craving new adventures, fresh experiences, and the thrill of what’s next. But deep down, I also long for stability. The moment life starts to feel a little settled or comfortable, something shifts. A new challenge shows up, uninvited. And honestly? It gets overwhelming.

Some days, I find myself crying quietly in the corner of my room. Other days, I throw on that tough-girl armor and push through. And sometimes, I just miss home deeply.

But if there’s one thing I’ve learned through it all, it’s that I never give up.
This time too, I’m choosing to take it one day at a time restarting, rebuilding, and realigning with life once again.

I’m endlessly grateful for the presence of my family, a handful of true friends who hold me up, and above all, my Mahadev who I know is writing every twist and turn of this beautiful, messy, meaningful story called My Life✨
